The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 26 July is 55,186 (6,387.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 21 July, there were 4,009 new confirmed cases (464.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 July, there were 3,200 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 25% (809 extra cases).
